programme.title: CHAOS WALKING
programme.desc: In the not too distant future, Todd Hewitt (Holland) discovers Viola (Ridley), a mysterious girl who crash lands on his planet, where all the women have disappeared, and the men are afflicted by “The Noise” – a force that puts all their thoughts on display. In this dangerous landscape, Viola’s life is threatened – and as Todd vows to protect her, he will have to discover his own inner power and unlock the planet’s dark secrets. From Doug Liman, director of The Bourne Identity and Edge of Tomorrow. Based on a best-selling novel trilogy, Chaos Walking is the film adaption of the first book “The Knife of Never Letting Go” written by Patrick Ness.

programme.title: ARGO
programme.desc: A real-life political intelligence dramedy based on a true story, this hostage rescue picture follows CIA "exfiltration" operative and master of disguise Tony Mendez who sets out to rescue a handful of American diplomats hiding out in 1979 Tehran. Pretending to be a film location scouting crew, Mendez and a motley crew of Hollywood artists, escape artists and con-artists smuggle the six embassy workers to safety in a daring rescue.

programme.title: DRILLBIT TAYLOR
programme.desc: Based on an original story by John Hughes, a trio of anxious high school freshmen is targeted by the school bully, Filkins, on the first day of school. Before they become completely engulfed in Filkins' reign of terror, they seek out protection by placing an ad for a personal bodyguard. Enter Drillbit Taylor, not the best but definitely the cheapest of the mercenaries, hit men and bodyguards. Drillbit is steely, dangerous and skilled in covert black-ops and exotic martial arts. He’s also a complete fraud who's no match for Filkins. Now it’s up to the trio to transform this down-and-out drifter into the savior he promised to be.

programme.title: ALVIN AND THE CHIPMUNKS
programme.desc: An advertising executive who longs to be a composer is befriended by three talking/singing chipmunks. After becoming the rambunctious rodents manager, he slowly but surely becomes something more -- their surrogate dad. But our hero doesn't realize how much he loves his furry kids until they are lured away by a manager who only cares about the money these talented woodland creatures can generate.

programme.title: MADAGASCAR 3: EUROPE'S MOST WANTED
programme.desc: In this second sequel to MADAGASCAR, Alex the Lion, Marty the Zebra, Melman the Giraffe and Gloria the Hippo join a traveling circus in an effort to get back home to New York.

programme.title: MY SUPER EX-GIRLFRIEND
programme.desc: Breaking up is hard to do--but it's particularly painful when your girlfriend has super-powers she can use on you! From director Ivan Reitman (Ghostbusters) comes this hilarious tale about a hapless architect who breaks things off with his superhero girlfriend, only to have her jealous, neurotic side come out in full force. Uma Thurman stars as pretty art-gallery owner Jenny, whose alter ego is the crime-fighting G-Girl; Luke Wilson is her unwitting boyfriend, who can't imagine the wrath he's unleashing by dumping her. Anna Faris, Eddie Izzard, Rainn Wilson and Wanda Sykes co-star. Directed by Ivan Reitman; screenplay by Don Payne.

programme.title: CRAZY, STUPID, LOVE
programme.desc: At forty, straight-laced Cal Weaver has dream job, a nice house, great kids and a marriage with his high school sweetheart. But when Cal learns that his wife, Emily, has cheated on him and wants a divorce, his "perfect" life quickly unravels. Now, spending his free evenings sulking alone at a local bar, the hapless Cal is taken on as wingman and protégé to a handsome player Jacob Palmer. In an effort to help Cal get over his wife and start living his life, Jacob opens Cal's eyes to the many options before him: flirty women, manly drinks and a sense of style. Cal and Emily aren't the only ones looking for love in what might be all the wrong places. The one thing that can't be made over is his heart, which seems to keep leading him back to where he began.

programme.title: JOURNEY TO THE CENTER OF THE EARTH (2008)
programme.desc: During a scientific expedition to Iceland, scientist Trevor Anderson, his nephew and their local guide are trapped in a cave – from which their only escape is to go deeper, into unimagined worlds. The trio comes face to face with never-before-seen creatures and harrowing dangers as they race against a volcanic eruption to reach the surface.

programme.title: JURASSIC WORLD
programme.desc: The Jurassic World theme park lets guests experience the thrill of witnessing actual dinosaurs, but something ferocious lurks behind the park’s attractions – a genetically modified dinosaur with savage capabilities. When the massive creature escapes, chaos erupts across the island. Now it’s up to Owen and Claire to save the park’s tourists from an all-out prehistoric assault.

programme.title: LARA CROFT TOMB RAIDER: THE CRADLE OF LIFE
programme.desc: Lara Croft is back and this time round she has discovered a truly historic find -- a luminous orb inscribed with hieroglyphics that can locate and unlock the mythical Pandora's Box, a box reputed to hold all the evils of the world within. A megalomaniac scientist, Jonathan Reiss, seeks to kill Lara and claim the orb as his own. Aided by mercenary and ex-lover Terry, Lara travels through Greece, East Africa, China, Hong Kong and England to save the orb from Reiss's hands. Whether in a black bikini or a figure-hugging silver suit, Lara means business, and she takes on the bad guys through loads of high-speed chases, explosions, hand-to-hand combat and shootouts.

programme.title: THE EQUALIZER 2
programme.desc: If you have a problem and nowhere else to turn, Robert McCall will help – he is The Equalizer. McCall has been aiding the beaten, exploited, and oppressed by serving an unflinching justice. But when McCall's dangerous past cuts especially close to home, he will need all of his skills to settle the score. This time, he must come face to face with highly trained assassins who will stop at nothing to destroy him.

programme.title: THE MARKSMAN
programme.desc: Hardened Arizona rancher Jim Hanson (Liam Neeson) simply wants to be left alone as he fends off eviction notices and tries to make a living on an isolated stretch of borderland. But everything changes when Hanson, an ex-Marine, witnesses an 11-year-old migrant, Miguel (Jacob Perez), fleeing with his mother Rosa (Teresa Ruiz) from drug cartel assassins led by the ruthless Mauricio (Juan Pablo Raba). After being caught in a shoot-out, an injured Rosa begs Jim to take her son to safety to her family in Chicago. Defying his step-daughter Sarah (Katheryn Winnick), Jim sneaks Miguel out of the local U.S. Customs and Border Patrol station and together, they hit the road with the group of killers in pursuit. Jim and Miguel slowly begin to overcome their differences and begin to forge an unlikely friendship, while Mauricio and his fellow assassins blaze a cold-blooded trail, hot on their heels.

programme.title: OBLIVION
programme.desc: On a spectacular future Earth that has evolved beyond recognition, one man’s confrontation with the past will lead him on a journey of redemption and discovery as he battles to save mankind.

programme.title: ROGUE
programme.desc: Megan Fox tackles a thrilling new role as a battle-hardened mercenary in this explosive action saga. As team leader O’Hara, she leads a lively squad of soldiers on a daring mission: rescue hostages from their captors in remote Africa. But as the mission goes awry and the team is stranded, O’Hara’s squad must face a bloody, brutal encounter with a gang of rebels—and the horde of ravenous, enraged lions they encounter.

programme.title: HOLLYWOOD ON SET 946
programme.desc: Each week Hollywood On Set goes behind-the-scenes and on the set on three major blockbusters in production, featuring action footage and interviews with actors and filmmakers to give you exclusive footage of the latest movies. Each episode gives you all the info on how and who made the movie. Each episode has a timeless quality.

programme.title: BLADE
programme.desc: Blade is a rebel in a world that exists beneath the surface of our own. A vampire leader, Deacon Frost, is preparing his vampire nation for the awakening of the Sleeper, who will lead them in the bloody battle to overthrow the human race. Only one thing stands in their way – Blade. Blade must confront not only the dark lords, but his own darker side as well, for he is growing weaker with his increasing increased longing for the sweet taste of blood.

programme.title: TAKING CHANCE
programme.desc: Based on the first-person account of US Marine Lieutenant Colonel Michael Strobl, this HBO Original Movie follows his poignant journey as the volunteer military escort officer assigned to accompany the body of a young fellow Marine killed in action in Iraq, across America back to his hometown of Dubois, Wyoming. Chronicling one of the silent, virtually unseen journeys that take place every day across the US, this drama bears witness to the fallen and all those who, literally and figuratively, carry them home.

programme.title: COLORS OF LOVE
programme.desc: When librarian Taylor Harris (Lowndes) suddenly loses her job, she moves back to her small hometown in Montana, where she gets involved in helping save her brother's small-town historic hotel from hometown guy and now tech tycoon Joel Sheenan (Murray) who wants to re-develop it.

programme.title: ROCKY
programme.desc: Rocky Balboa is a Philadelphia club fighter who seems to be going nowhere. But when a stroke of fate puts him in the ring with a world heavyweight champion, Rocky knows that it's his one shot at the big time; a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to go the distance and come out a winner!

programme.title: GAME CHANGE
programme.desc: This HBO Original Movie offers a searing behind-the-scenes look at John McCain’s presidential campaign: from the selection of Alaska Governor Sarah Palin as McCain’s vice presidential running mate, to their defeat in the general election. Told through the eyes of McCain strategist, Steve Schmidt, Game Change pulls back the curtain on the intense human drama surrounding the 2008 US election, revealing the uncertainty surrounding the decisions made behind closed doors, examining the chain of events that would determine the leadership of the country, offering a unique glimpse into the inner workings of a historic campaign.

programme.title: THE GILDED AGE S1 02: MONEY ISN'T EVERYTHING
programme.desc: Tom Raikes' visit to New York delights Marian but worries aunt Agnes. An increasingly desperate Peggy seeks legal advice from Mr. Raikes, George takes steps to further his latest business plans, Oscar van Rhijn homes in on young Gladys Russell, and a charity bazaar becomes the source of a dramatic stand after Bertha is slighted.

programme.title: BRIDESMAIDS
programme.desc: A girl asked to be the maid of honor at her best friend’s wedding must face off with an alpha bridesmaid, a woman who clearly wants to take over her job and her best friend status. A riotously hilarious and emotionally affecting glance at the importance of female relationships and the humorous pain that comes when we realize our lives are not advancing at the same rate as our friends’.

programme.title: THE HIGH NOTE
programme.desc: A superstar singer and her overworked personal assistant are presented with a choice that could alter the course of their respective careers.

programme.title: THE FEVER
programme.desc: In this HBO Original Movie about the high cost of enlightenment and the ever-widening gap between rich and poor, Vanessa Redgrave plays a nameless woman from a privileged world who suffers from a sense of disconnection from her comfortable life, travels to a nameless country in the throes of civil war. Suddenly deliriously ill, she confronts an internal chorus of conflicting voices: dreams of comfort from her past, images of violence, accusations of indifference, and cold-blooded arguments in favour of oppression. The central question is: what, if anything, is a morally consistent way to live in the world as it is?

programme.title: AS YOU LIKE IT
programme.desc: Witty, playful and utterly magical, the story is a compelling romantic adventure in which Rosalind and Orlando’s celebrated courtship is played out against a backdrop of political rivalry, banishment and exile in the Forest of Arden – all set in 19th century Japan, when the country first opened up for trade with the West, and merchant adventurers arrived there from all over the world.

programme.title: SIX MINUTES TO MIDNIGHT
programme.desc: In the summer of 1939, influential families in Nazi Germany have sent their young daughters to a finishing school in the idyllic English coastal town of Bexhill-on-Sea to learn the English language, etiquette, refinement and be ambassadors for a forward-looking National Socialist party (Nazi). Under the watchful eye of their headmistress, Miss Rocholl, and her devoted assistant, Ilse Keller, the girls practise their manners and learn how to represent the ideal example of German womanhood. But shortly before the start of World War II, an English teacher from the school disappears. British intelligence agent Thomas Miller is sent undercover into the school disguised as a teacher to find out what had happened to the missing man. It triggers a sequence of deadly espionage events where people are not who they appear to be and leaves Miller being pursued for murder by the local police. Loosely based on a true story.

programme.title: AMERICAN SNIPER
programme.desc: Navy SEAL Chris Kyle (Bradley Cooper) is sent to Iraq with only one mission: to protect his brothers-in-arms. His pinpoint accuracy saves countless lives on the battlefield and, as stories of his courageous exploits spread, he earns the nickname “Legend.” However, his reputation is also growing behind enemy lines, putting a price on his head and making him a prime target of insurgents. He is also facing a different kind of battle on the home front: striving to be a good husband and father from halfway around the world.Despite the danger, as well as the toll on his family at home, Chris serves through four harrowing tours of duty in Iraq, personifying the spirit of the SEAL creed to “leave no one behind.” But upon returning to his wife, Taya (Sienna Miller), and kids, Chris finds that it is the war he can’t leave behind.

programme.title: KAJILLIONAIRE
programme.desc: From acclaimed writer/director Miranda July comes a profoundly moving and wildly original comedy. Con-artists Theresa (Debra Winger) and Robert (Richard Jenkins) have spent 26 years training their only daughter, Old Dolio (Evan Rachel Wood), to swindle, scam, and steal at every opportunity. During a desperate, hastily conceived heist, they charm a stranger (Gina Rodriguez) into joining their next scam, only to have their entire world turned upside down.

programme.title: ASSAULT ON PRECINCT 13
programme.desc: Ethan Hawke and Laurence Fishburne lead an all-star cast, including John Leguizamo, Ja Rule and Drea de Matteo, in the explosive, action-packed thriller, Assault on Precinct 13. Run-down Precinct 13 is about to close its doors forever. But everything changes when some of Detroit's most lethal prisoners arrive. Soon, the only thing more dangerous than the criminals on the inside is the rogue gang on the outside. To survive the night, two men on opposite sides of the law will have to work together to battle an enemy who doesn't follow the code of cop or criminal.

programme.title: THE AVIATOR
programme.desc: They were a new breed of hero, the men who flew the first transcontinental mail planes in the 1920s. Christopher Reeve stars as one of those courageous pilots. Rosanna Arquette is his teenage passenger, whose fighting spirit becomes a key to survival--and a spark for romance--when the plane is downed in a mountain wilderness.

programme.title: ATONEMENT
programme.desc: Based on the critically acclaimed best seller by Ian McEwan, Atonement tells the tale of a writer from her childhood through to her adulthood. As a 13-year-old child, Briony Tallis sets in motion a chain of events that have devastating repercussions on the lives of her sister Cecilia Tallis and her lover Robbie Turner. The film charts the events over a number of decades, carefully documenting the consequences of Briony's actions. Atonement is a spellbinding movie that will haunt you with a combination of brilliant cinematography and storytelling.

programme.title: SAFE HOUSE
programme.desc: In this high tension, action-packed thriller, a lethal prisoner, who is escorted by a CIA agent, must make his way from a compromised safe house to another one in South Africa without being taken out by violent forces that want them both dead. Pursued by shadowy figures that conspire to stop them, the pair, unsure of who to trust, has to make the uneasy decision of relying on each other.

programme.title: RED EYE
programme.desc: Desk manager of a Miami hotel, Lisa Reisert found herself a pawn in a terrorist attack whilst onboard a flight.

programme.title: BOOGIE
programme.desc: From acclaimed writer, producer and restauranteur Eddie Huang comes his directorial debut Boogie, the coming-of-age story of Alfred "Boogie" Chin (Taylor Takahashi), a basketball phenom living in Queens, New York, who dreams of one day playing in the NBA. While his parents pressure him to focus on earning a scholarship to an elite college, Boogie must find a way to navigate a new girlfriend, high school, on-court rivals and the burden of expectation.

programme.title: AEONFLUX
programme.desc: Four hundred years into the future, half of the human population has been wiped out by a virus, except for one last protected city of mankind. Aeon Flux is a professional assassin sent to kill the leader of this city. But she uncovers an insidious plot and ends up defending her prey.

programme.title: HOT PURSUIT
programme.desc: An uptight and by-the-book cop tries to protect the sexy and outgoing widow of a drug boss as they race through Texas, pursued by crooked cops and murderous gunmen.

programme.title: MONTE CARLO
programme.desc: Grace (Selena Gomez) is an ordinary girl who becomes an accidental princess when a family summer trip to Paris turns into the fantasy of a lifetime. Living like royalty, Grace, along with her two best friends, discovers who she really is – by assuming another person’s identity.

programme.title: BAD NEWS BEARS
programme.desc: A modern remake of the 1976 classic, it tells you the story of Morris Buttermaker, a foul-mouthed yet good-hearted baseball coach who agrees to coach an inept Little League team that needs to learn the art of winning.

programme.title: LOVE ACTUALLY
programme.desc: "Get ready for fun!" (Leah Rozen, People) with the "feel good movie of the year!" (Clay Smith, Access Hollywood) Love Actually is the ultimate romantic comedy from the makers of Bridget Jones's Diary and Notting Hill. Funny, irresistible and heartwarming, an all-star cast (Hugh Grant, Liam Neeson, Colin Firth and Emma Thompson, to name a few!) will take you on a breathtaking tour of love's delightful twists and turns. Fall under the spell of Love Actually and share the laughs and charm again and again.

programme.title: BOOGIE
programme.desc: From acclaimed writer, producer and restauranteur Eddie Huang comes his directorial debut Boogie, the coming-of-age story of Alfred "Boogie" Chin (Taylor Takahashi), a basketball phenom living in Queens, New York, who dreams of one day playing in the NBA. While his parents pressure him to focus on earning a scholarship to an elite college, Boogie must find a way to navigate a new girlfriend, high school, on-court rivals and the burden of expectation.

programme.title: HARRIET
programme.desc: Based on the thrilling and inspirational life of an iconic American freedom fighter, Harriet tells the extraordinary tale of Harriet Tubman's escape from slavery and transformation into one of America's greatest heroes. Haunted by memories of those she left behind, Harriet (Cynthia Erivo) ventures back into dangerous territory on a mission to lead others to freedom. With allies like abolitionist William Still (Leslie Odom, Jr.) and the entrepreneurial Marie Buchanon (Janelle Monae), Harriet risks capture and death to guide hundreds to safety as one of the most prominent conductors of the Underground Railroad. Witness the story of a woman who defied impossible odds to change the course of her life and the fate of the nation.

programme.title: THE GIRL WITH THE DRAGON TATTOO
programme.desc: Mikael Blomkvist, a disgraced investigative journalist, leaves his magazine business to his co-owner and takes up an offer to investigate the 40 year old case of industrialist Henrik Vanger's missing niece. To help him with the case, Blomkvist takes the help of a young hacker named Lisbeth Salander. Together, they uncover many secrets of the Vanger family.

programme.title: YOU SHOULD HAVE LEFT
programme.desc: Kevin Bacon and Amanda Seyfried star as a couple seeking a restful vacation in a remote home in the Welsh countryside. What at first seems like a perfect retreat distorts into a terrifying nightmare when reality begins to unravel, dark episodes from the past resurface, and a sinister force in the house refuses to let them leave.

programme.title: SEARCH AND DESTROY
programme.desc: When American Ranger John Cutter fails to save a family being held hostage and loses his entire team in a battle with the infamous Arms Dealer Igor Rodin, John is discharged from the army. Three years later he is approached by his old General to go on a private contract mission when Igor resurfaces to seek revenge.

programme.title: TERMINAL INVASION
programme.desc: The action begins when a group of outer-space aliens, disguised as humans, take over a small rural airport in preparation for conquering the Earth. The fate of mankind ultimately rests in the hands of two others trapped in the terminal: a fiercely combative female pilot named Cathy Garrett, and a convicted murderer named Jack. The only problem is, with the aliens totally camouflaged as earthlings, no one can tell the good guys from the bad!

programme.title: POSEIDON
programme.desc: It's New Year's Eve, and over 2000 people are celebrating the moment onboard a luxury cruise liner, Poseidon. At the stroke of midnight, a huge rogue wave hits the ship and rolls it upside down. Against the captain's orders to stay put and wait for rescue, a group of survivors make their way out of the wreckage, determined to save themselves from imminent death.

programme.title: ENTRAPMENT
programme.desc: Following the theft of a valuable piece of artwork, Gin Baker, an insurance agent, convinces her employers to allow her to befriend an aging master thief, in order to better protect their clients.

programme.title: WRONG TURN AT TAHOE
programme.desc: Joshua is a tough-as-nails collector for the mob who one fateful day gets caught in the middle of a double-cross involving the biggest drug lord in the business. How do you escape when you have nowhere to run? You lock and load and get ready for an action-packed thrill ride that will keep you on the edge of your seat!

programme.title: MORLOCKS
programme.desc: A time machine opens a window into the future and the Morlocks, a monster species, uses it to come back to the present. Prepare for a rampage.

programme.title: THE PERFECT SCORE
programme.desc: A coming-of-age story that follows six high school students from diverse backgrounds as they conspire to steal the answers to the SAT. They quickly realize that the answer to their problems and the key to their happiness do not lie in achieving a perfect score.

programme.title: SPACE JAM
programme.desc: Two great superstars – basketball legend Michael Jordan and Hollywood legend Bugs Bunny – team up for the looniest interplanetary basketball game ever played. Nasty aliens kidnap a bunch of Looney Tunes characters to display in an outer-space theme park. To save his friends, Bugs challenges the bad guys for a game of basketball, and then recruits Michael Jordan to help bring them down in defeat!

programme.title: COACH CARTER
programme.desc: Based on the life of a controversial high school basketball coach Ken Carter, who made national news in 1999 when he benched his entire undefeated basketball team for poor academic performance. The coach forfeited two league games and made the gym off-limits until his students raised their grades – a move that drew both praise and criticism from parents and school officials.

programme.title: THE HANGOVER
programme.desc: When a group of friends gets together for one last weekend-long bachelor party in Vegas, they think they had a good time. But it's very hard to remember, and they are suffering the dreadful after-effects of girls, party and alcohol. And then they realize they have somehow lost the groom! Now, they must struggle to retrace their wild weekend to find their friend and deliver the bridegroom to his wedding -- even as they suffer from one killer Hangover!

programme.title: THE HANGOVER PART II
programme.desc: Ready for another round? In the follow-up to the record-breaking hit comedy, Phil, Stu, Alan and Doug travel to exotic Thailand for Stu's wedding. After Doug's now-unforgettable Las Vegas bachelor party, Stu is not taking any chances and has opted for a safe and subdued pre-wedding brunch. Things don't always go as planned however. What happens in Vegas may stay in Vegas, but what happens in Bangkok can't even be imagined – think monkeys, tattoos and the return of Mr. Chow!

programme.title: THE HANGOVER PART III
programme.desc: When one of their buddies is kidnapped by an angry gangster, the Wolfpack must find Mr. Chow, who has escaped from prison and is on the run. An epic finale to the Hangover trilogy in which the guys must finish what they started by going back to where it all began: Las Vegas.
